SIMPLE: reflected
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Reflected
<hw>Re*flect"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Thrown back after
striking a surface; <as>as, <ex>reflected</ex> light, heat, sound,
etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence: Not one's own; received from another; <as>as,
his glory was <ex>reflected</ex> glory</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Bent backward or outward; reflexed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reflectent</ent>⟦br⟧
